\begin_layout Section*
Theory and methodology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Data collection
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For this project, we will scrape job listings from the Danish job portal
 Jobindex in the period 2015-2020.
 More specifically, we will scrape the job title, company, and a preview
 of the full job listing.
 These are all available on Jobindex's search results page (see Figure 1).
 Ideally, we would have liked to scrape the full job listing and not just
 the preview.
 However, doing so would require scraping not only Jobindex but also different
 company websites and PDFs with varying HTML structure; and although we
 wrote a program that should be able of achieving this, once we started
 running it we realized this would take more time than what we had available
 for the project.
 It is also due to these same time constraints that we decided not to extend
 the sample period any further than 2010-2020.
 Notice that since all current and archived job listings in Jobindex are
 publicly available and do not contain any personal data, we could not think
 of any ethical breaches to take into consideration before scraping the
 data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

