\begin_layout Subsection*
Sample controls
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Validating the accuracy of our keywords in identifying remote listings
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We would like to get an idea of how accurate our keywords are in identifying
 remote job listings, ie.
 whether our sample actually consists of job listings where working remotely
 is advertised, or if it is capturing the keywords being used in other contexts.
 To do so, we draw 5 random samples consisting of 10 job listings each.
 For each listing, we go into Jobindex and read the full job description
 to check whether the possbility of working remotely is actually mentioned.
 The results of this exercise can be found in the table below.
 Note that 80% of the joblistings we counted as fails weren't true fails,
 but cases where we couldn't get access to the full job listing either due
 to the link being broken or because Jobindex couldn't retrieve a copy of
 the full job listing.
 Despite this, we found that on average, we had correctly identified remote
 job listings 80% of the time and the results were fairly robust across
 samples, ranging from 70%-90% accuracy.
 
\end_layout

