\begin_layout Standard
Overall, remote job postings constitute less than one pct.
 of the total job postings published in a given year from 2010 to 2020.
 The percentage level is quite constant around 0.5-0.6 pct.
 up until 2019, and then incresing to almost 0.9 pct.
 of all job postings published in 2020.
 Historically, job postings containing words that indicate remote work have
 especially been within Sales and communiation, and when taking a closer
 look at samples from the dataset, many of these are driving salesmen.
 However, since 2015, an increasing share of the remote job postings are
 within Information Technology and Office and finance, which are generally
 more characterized as 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

desk jobs
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 that the worker can do from home.
 At the other end of the spectrum, we find a low share of job postings containin
g words that indicate remote work within Industry and Craft, Teaching and
 Social and Health, i.e.
 occupations that require the presence of the worker to perform the job.
\end_layout

