\begin_layout Standard
The first thing that comes to mind when looking at Table 2 is how similar
 the words are across languages.
 Both in English and Danish, sales is the most used word across .
 We see that Copenhagen is mentioned quite often, which is in line with
 the trend we saw before whereby remote positions tend to concentrate around
 in the capital.
 The fact that the word 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

mulighed (possibility)
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is included when advertising for remote jobs suggests that working remotely
 is often used as a selling point to make a position more attractive to
 applicants.
 Take for example the following snippet taken from Jobindex and translated
 to English: 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Your work will take place in our office in Copenhagen, but there will be
 a possibility of working from home
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Dit arbejdet vil foregå fra vores kontor i København, men der vil være mulighed
 for hjemmearbejde
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

 By signaling to job seekers that there is a possibility of working partly
 or fully remotely, employers can expand their pool of applicants across
 geographical location but also socioeconomic background.
 Evidence of this has been found previously, for example a 2017
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "key-1"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 study about women working in tech found that 76% of women surveyed listed
 remote working opportunities as top priority.
 Moreover, the most frequent words in job listings can be grouped around
 two major areas or themes, namely IT and sales.
 This is not surprising given what we have seen in the descriptive analysis.
 However, one could imagine that not all jobs related to sales and IT can
 be performed remotely, and we would like to know with more detail which
 type of jobs are being advertised as remote.
 For this, we extract the top 10 most common words used in the titles from
 job listings, where the name of the position is often mentioned.
 The same procedure as with the preview of the job listings is followed
 and the results can be found in the table below.
 Once again, these words are fairly similar across country.
 They both have 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

manager
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 as the most frequent word, which together with the word 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

sap
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, which in this context most likely refers to Systems Applications and Products
 in Data Processing software, suggests remote jobs are mostly advertised
 for management positions.
 Moreover, for IT, remote job listings center around senior positions as
 suggested by words like 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

senior
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

specialist
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

erfaren(experienced)
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

consultant
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, while more ambiguous words like 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

engineer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

developer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

teknisk
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 could also be used in the context of entry-level jobs.
 In the case of sales, this analysis doesn't get us much further than before.
\end_layout

